Note that I've added a closing tag for the `body` style rule and corrected some minor syntax errors. I've also added a comment to indicate where your calculator HTML content should go. Please replace the comment with your actual calculator HTML code.

The copy button is located in the following section of the code:

```html
/* ─── COPY BUTTON ─── */
(function(){
  var d=document.getElementById('display');if(!d)return;
  var b=document.createElement('button');b.className='v30cb';b.id='v30CB';b.title='Copy result';b.textContent='COPY';
  b.onclick=function(){
    var v=(document.getElementById('mainLine')||{}).textContent||'';
    if(!v||v==='0'){var be=(document.getElementById('exprBefore')||{}).textContent||'';var ae=(document.getElementById('exprAfter')||{}).textContent||'';v=(be+ae).trim();}
    if(!v)return;
    navigator.clipboard.writeText(v).then(function(){b.textContent='✓ COPIED';b.classList.add('cp');setTimeout(function(){b.textContent='COPY';b.classList.remove('cp');},1500);}).catch(function(){});
  };
  d.appendChild(b);
})();
```

This code creates a button with the text "COPY" and appends it to the element with the id "display". When the button is clicked, it copies the text from the element with the id "mainLine" (or the combined text from the elements with the ids "exprBefore" and "exprAfter" if "mainLine" is empty) to the clipboard. The button's text then changes to "✓ COPIED" for 1.5 seconds before reverting back to "COPY".

To ensure everything works offline after the first load, the existing code that caches resources for offline use should be sufficient:

```html
// Cache resources for offline use
window.addEventListener('load', function() {
  caches.open('calculator-resources').then(function(cache) {
    cache.addAll([
      'calculator.css',
      'calculator.js',
      'font-awesome.css',
      'font-awesome.js',
    ]);
  });
});
```

Additionally, the following code handles the offline mode:

```html
// Ensure everything works offline after first load
window.addEventListener('offline', function() {
  console.log('Offline mode: using cached resources');
});
```

No further modifications are needed in this section to support offline functionality.
